edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.util

Interface ILogger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoggerFactory

    public interface ILogger
    Provides logging, debugging, and tracing capabilities common to interpreters. Debugging will show full error messages and stacktraces. Tracing will capture the parser and transform XML stages in log files.

      • getPrintStream

        PrintStream getPrintStream(String streamName)
                    throws IOException
        Get the PrintStream associated with a logger stream name. If streamName is null or empty, or not found in the streamMap, uses getOut(). If the logger stream is already open, uses it from the cache. Otherwise, will use streamName to lookup the filename in the streamMap and open it.
        Throws:
        IOException
